<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1727,2042]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">
The 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[203,393,1727,1753]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">
<emphasis box="[203,393,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Neotrygon kuhlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex has recently been expanded (Last 
<emphasis box="[981,1039,1727,1753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2016). These taxonomic revisions, however, did not consider Bay of Bengal specimens in detail. To date, two species have been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,285,1799,1825]" name="Bangladesh" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Bangladesh</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pavan-Kumar, Kumar, Pitale, Shen &amp; Borsa" authorityYear="2017" box="[299,405,1799,1825]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[299,405,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">N. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[465,565,1799,1825]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">
<emphasis box="[465,565,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">N. kuhlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Haque, A. B. &amp; Das, S. A. &amp; Biswas, A. R." box="[582,807,1799,1825]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" pagination="0222273" refId="ref6570" refString="Haque, A. B., Das, S. A. &amp; Biswas, A. R. (2019 a) DNA analysis of elasmobranch products originating from Bangladesh reveals unregulated elasmobranch fishery and trade on species of global conservation concern. PloS one, 14 (9), e 0222273. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0222273" type="journal article" year="2019">
Haque 
<emphasis box="[667,726,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2019a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hoq, M. E. &amp; Haroon, A. Y. &amp; Hussain, M. G." box="[821,1008,1799,1826]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" refId="ref6837" refString="Hoq, M. E., Haroon, A. Y. &amp; Hussain, M. G. (2011) Shark fisheries in the Bay of Bengal, Bangladesh: Status and potentialities. Support to Sustainable Management of the BOBLME Project, Bangladesh Fisheries Research Institute, 76 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Hoq 
<emphasis box="[879,939,1799,1825]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). In this present study, a total of 
<specimenCount pageId="7" pageNumber="218" type="generic">649 specimens</specimenCount>
were examined, and five sampled for genetic analysis. Morphological differences were observed, including the dorsal coloration and tail banding. Several specimens were most consistent with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Last, White &amp; Seret" authorityYear="2016" box="[1201,1429,1871,1897]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caeruleopunctata">
<emphasis box="[1201,1429,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">N. caeruleopunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but have been preliminarily identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Last, White &amp; Seret" authorityYear="2016" box="[618,885,1907,1933]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caeruleopunctata">
<emphasis box="[618,645,1908,1933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">N.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[689,885,1907,1933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">caeruleopunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[901,998,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,888,912]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,187,864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@8.[151,1436,181,864]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Dorsal and ventral image of Neotrygon cf. caeruleopunctata from Coxâ€™s Bazar (Female, DW= 30.48 cm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5448240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5448240/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Figure 5</figureCitation>
) due to possible genetic differences in the Bay of Bengal specimens. It is likely that previous records of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[877,973,1943,1969]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">
<emphasis box="[877,973,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">N. kuhlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent this species, with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[1286,1382,1943,1969]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">
<emphasis box="[1286,1382,1943,1969]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">N. kuhlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now considered to occur only from the 
<collectingCountry box="[540,731,1979,2005]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
, and adjacent island groups (
<bibRefCitation author="Last, P. &amp; Naylor, G. &amp; Seret, B. &amp; White, W. &amp; de Carvalho, M. &amp; Stehmann, M." box="[1058,1253,1979,2006]" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" refId="ref7175" refString="Last, P., Naylor, G., Seret, B., White, W., de Carvalho, M. &amp; Stehmann, M. (2016 a) Rays of the World. CSIRO publishing, Melbourne, ix + 790 pp." type="book" year="2016">
Last 
<emphasis box="[1115,1172,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
). All genetically sampled specimens were labelled as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bay" authorityName="Bay" box="[562,733,2016,2042]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Neotrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="218" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[562,680,2016,2041]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="218">Neotrygon</emphasis>
Bay
</taxonomicName>
of Bengal variants.
</paragraph>
